    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.1: \"AMPA receptor CTs associate directly with AP2μ\"\nFig.3: \"Direct high-affinity binding of μ2-adaptin to the GluR2 CT\"\nFig.4: \"The GluR2-derived AP-2μ binding peptide targets a synaptotagmin 1 ΔC2B chimeric reporter protein for internalization\"\nFig.5: \"The Syt-1 AP-2 binding peptide increases mEPSC amplitude and frequency\". Experimental description: - Species of overexpressed AP2mu is not stated in the paper. Authors were contacted (dd 13/3/2018, haucke@fmp-berlin.de). Answer:\n\n\"Dear Pim,\nBoth were from rat (e.g. AP2mu was rat as were hippocampal neurons in culture).\nBest wishes,\nVolker\"\n\n- Authors refer to AP2mu siRNA \"AAGUGGAUGCCUUUCGGGUCA\" used in A. Motley et al., 2003 (PMID:12952941). Nucleotide BLAST matches AP2M1",
